    "body": "## Problem\n\n:%s/    / /g -- only picks up one, and two spaces to find, and replace;\nI have to literally copy the white spaces (more than two of them) I want to find, and paste them into the regular expression, before it will find them, and replace them with one space, which is what I want;\nNothing else works whether using /\\s+ or anything else..\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\nAs aforesaid\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nThat nvim will find the successive empty white spaces, and replace them with a single space, or anything else..\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim (Lazyvim) version (nvim -v): `v0.12.0-dev-1769 gd6bee7e407` neovim/neovim@d6bee7e407\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: Yes\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.17.9-arch1-1\n- Terminal name/version: kitty\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-kitty`\n- Installation: Vanilla Arch Linux: 6.17.9-arch1-1 #1 SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Mon, 24 Nov 2025 15:21:09 +0000 x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n",
